[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = ThermodynamicalRigorous","category":"page"},{"location":"#ThermodynamicalRigorous","page":"Home","title":"ThermodynamicalRigorous","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for ThermodynamicalRigorous.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [ThermodynamicalRigorous]","category":"page"},{"location":"#ThermodynamicalRigorous.difference-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"ThermodynamicalRigorous.difference","text":"difference(T, x)\n\nCompute the value of the function (T(x_n)-x₁ T(x_n-1)-x_n  T(x_1)-x_2)  a zero of this function is a periodic orbit of period n for the dynamic T. It is worth observing that n is inferred from the array x`.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using ThermodynamicalRigorous\n\njulia> T(x) = 0<=x<0.5 ? 2*x : 2*x-1\nT (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia> difference(T, 1)\n1-element Vector{Int64}:\n 0\n\njulia> difference(T, [0, 0, 0])\n3-element Vector{Int64}:\n 0\n 0\n 0\n\njulia> difference(T, [0.2 0.4 0.8 0.6])\n4-element Vector{Float64}:\n  0.0\n  0.0\n  1.1102230246251565e-16\n -5.551115123125783e-17\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
